choices.text:
Harmony used discarded paper to make notepads for her friends. She would fold five letter size pieces of paper three times then cut along the lines. She would then stack the smaller note papers and staple them together. How long would one notepad last if someone wrote ten notes per day?
Harmoney used discarded paper to make notepads for her friends, following a method known as 'folding three times' and 'cutting along lines'. After folding the letters in five sizes (three times), she cut them down along their length. Then, she stacked these smaller papers one on top of each other until they were all stapled together at an angle. 

One notepad would last for aproximately 150 days if ten notes per day are written to it.
